snippet: The dark hallway that takes audiences into the Comedy Cellar, the most storied old-school comedy club in the city, has the look of a hall of fame, even if it isn’t one.
abstract: Jason Zinoman Still Life column sketches an image of the Comedy Cellar's entrance hallway, which is lined with head shots of comedians who have performed there.
lead_paragraph: The dark hallway that takes audiences into the Comedy Cellar, the most storied old-school comedy club in the city, has the look of a hall of fame, even if it isn’t one.
